cran_state: planned
next: medfit **0.3.2** released to `main` (PR #52/#53/#54), tagged `v0.3.2` on commit `9b4d377` as a GitHub pre-release, tarball attached. Win-builder re-dispatch **confirmed clean** 2026-07-21: R-release 4.5.3 + R-devel r90283 both `Status: OK`, 0 NOTEs — cran-comments.md and the pre-release notes updated to match. `cran-prep` verdict: ready, 0 blockers. Only remaining step: `devtools::submit_cran()` (maintainer-manual: interactive TTY + email click) — or the web form at https://cran.r-project.org/submit.html. On acceptance: promote the pre-release to full (`gh release edit v0.3.2 --prerelease=false --latest`). Unblocks Stage 2 / probmed (Imports medfit ≥0.3.0). Independent now: medrobust CRAN prep (6 TODOs + NEWS/DESCRIPTION drift); RMediation 1.6.1 also ready (see its own .STATUS) — both queued for manual `devtools::submit_cran()`.
aspell_iteration: DESCRIPTION-only aspell NOTE took 2 rounds to fully explain — round 1 fixed "VanderWeele" (PR #51/#53), win-builder recheck then surfaced a DIFFERENT note on "RMediation medrobust probmed" (same DESCRIPTION text, unchanged) instead of clearing to 0 notes; extended `.aspell/defaults.R`'s ignore list to all 4 words (PR #54). Root cause of the note "moving" rather than clearing is unconfirmed (likely win-builder-side aspell dictionary/environment variance across separate check runs, not a code regression — git diff -w confirmed no DESCRIPTION text change between rounds). Either outcome (0 notes or 1 explained note) is CRAN-submission-safe.
version_bump: 0.3.1→0.3.2 (2026-07-20) — discovered mid-`/rforge:r:submit` that an UNRELEASED-to-CRAN `v0.3.1` GitHub tag already existed (published 2026-06-12, "Latest", pointing at an older commit); no `R/` code changed since that tag (`git diff -w` empty — this is a patch-level CI/lint/CRAN-compliance release, same shape as 0.2.0→0.2.1). Bumped to 0.3.2 to avoid colliding with/moving the existing public tag. CRAN itself only needs 0.2.1→0.3.2 to be valid, which it is.
ci_flake_fixed: `ubuntu-latest (release, noSuggests)` job failed twice with "no package called 'testthat'" on identical commits (PR #52 + its main merge) — root cause: `dependencies: "hard"` excludes Suggests for extra-packages too, so testthat install was left to chance. Fixed by pinning `any::testthat` explicitly in `.github/workflows/R-CMD-check.yaml` (commit 8e23a0a, via a spawned background session) — confirmed clean on PR #53 and its main merge, no more reruns needed.
lint_gate: ⚠️ 2026-07-16 — lintr 3.4.0 (published 00:10 that day) tightened `indentation_linter` and turned the `lint` job RED on every PR, days before the 0.3.1 CRAN window. CI installs lintr fresh from RSPM each run and sets LINTR_ERROR_ON_LINT=true, so an upstream release can break the gate overnight with no local change: identical R code passed on 3.3.x (#48, 06-22) and failed on 3.4.0 (#49, 07-16). FIXED by PR #50 — reindented 11 function signatures 4→2 spaces (whitespace only; `git diff -w` empty; 806 tests pass). NOT configurable away: no `indentation_linter` setting accommodates 4-space (hanging_indent_style tidy/always/never = 1/2/8 lints), and `styler --strict` produces 2-space too, so lintr 3.4.0 aligned with tidyverse's own formatter rather than regressing. Lesson: verify `lint` green immediately before any CRAN submission — a passing run from weeks ago proves nothing.
cran_0.3.1_check: ✅ 2026-07-20 — strict incoming-CRAN check (--as-cran --run-donttest, DEPENDS_ONLY/SUGGESTS_ONLY, CRAN_INCOMING_REMOTE) = 0/0/0 locally after 3 fixes: Date field bump (37f14f6), `.Rbuildignore` `.remember` leak — also fixed across mediationverse/medrobust/missingmed/rmediation, probmed+medsim already had it (37f14f6 + 4 sibling-repo commits), aspell WORDLIST gaps + 1 hyphenation reword (9980bb6). `urlchecker::url_check()` clean (17/17). Reverse-dep check: RMediation (only CRAN revdep, Suggests-only) 307/307 tests pass against 0.3.1. Win-builder (all 3 flavors: R-release 4.6.1, R-oldrelease 4.5.3, R-devel r90279) all report the SAME 1 NOTE — "Possibly misspelled words in DESCRIPTION: VanderWeele" (cited author surname; local check missed it, no `aspell` binary on this machine — see CLAUDE.md). FIXED via `.aspell/defaults.R` (`description <- list(ignore = c("VanderWeele"))`, PR #51, merged 431c1e5, feature/aspell-ignore-description worktree cleaned up) — not yet re-verified against a live aspell/win-builder round, but even if it recurs it's CRAN-safe to submit with as an explained NOTE. `cran-comments.md` resynced (c84eedb, then updated post-#51). **Submission-ready.**
done: 2026-06-22: gitignored devtools CRAN-SUBMISSION artifact (anchored /CRAN-SUBMISSION) + removed stale v0.2.0 marker — PR #47 merged to dev (10/10 CI green). Stage-1 cascade COMPLETE (2026-06-18); medfit 0.2.1 on CRAN. RMediation 1.5.0 released (GitHub, pre-release strict checks 0/0/0 ✅) + CRAN-submitted 2026-06-20 (pkg_id 345448, awaiting acceptance). mediationverse + medsim: Remotes dropped, medfit ≥0.2.0 pinned.
watcher: Daily remote routine "medfit-cran-watch" (trig_018qiNZMTUP5Az2UGXyv6vRf, 9am America/Denver) checks the CRAN page + Gmail and reports ACCEPTED / ACTION REQUIRED / STILL PENDING. Runs: https://claude.ai/code/routines/trig_018qiNZMTUP5Az2UGXyv6vRf
extensions: Ext A (parallel mediation) COMPLETE — class (#34), lm/glm extractor+confint (#36), lavaan extractor+vignette+pkgdown (#37) ALL MERGED to dev. Structural trio (simple/serial/parallel) now closed across lm/glm + lavaan. Ext B (VanderWeele 4-way interaction) COMPLETE — spec at planning/specs/SPEC-interaction-fourway-2026-06-03.md. PR B1 (InteractionMediationData class, 35 tests, #38) + PR B2a (lm/glm extraction + decomposition/m_star + delta confint, 27 tests, #39) + PR B2b (lavaan extraction + vignette, 22 tests, #40) ALL MERGED to dev. Four-way decomposition (CDE/INTref/INTmed/PIE) now ships across lm/glm + lavaan. NEXT: Ext C (engine adapters/CMAverse), needs SPEC-engine-registry.md + SPEC-cmaverse-adapter.md. Toolchain: roxygen2 8.0.0 migration = issue #35.
